changed.description: Fired when a property is changed.

screenResized.description: Triggered when the viewport size is changed

screenPaddingBottom.description: Padding applied to the bottom of the viewport by Teverse.

screenPaddingLeft.description: Padding applied to the left of the viewport by Teverse.

mousePosition.description: Absolute position of cursor in pixels

screenPaddingTop.description: Padding applied to the top of the viewport by Teverse. Mostly on devices with notches.

screenSize.description: Absolute size of the viewport measured in pixels

screenPaddingRight.description: Padding applied to the right of the viewport by Teverse.

imageAlpha.description: An alpha value of 1.0 is completely visible, 0.0 is invisible.

imageBottomRight.description: Defaults to {1, 1}, the bottom right corner of the image loaded. Decreasing this number leads to cropping, increasing will lead to repetition.

rolloffFactor.description: Rolloff rate for the source, default is 1.0

offset.description: The offset of the track in seconds

maxDistance.description: Audio will not be audible beyond this distance in 3D Space

loop.description: When true, the audio is repeated until manually stopped

gain.description: Controls the loudness of the audio

destroy.description: Destroys this object, further accessing this instance will error

changed.description: Fired when a property is changed.

childAdded.description: Triggered when the viewport size is changed

mouseEnter.description: Mouse is hovering over this element

destroying.description: Triggered when the object is destroyed

childRemoved.description: Triggered when a child is added

zIndex.description: Increasing the zIndex will render this element above others. Currently a signed 16 bit integer.

active.description: When true, this element can capture the mouse's hover

clip.description: When true, children are cropped to fit

parent.description: Parent of a guiBase must be another gui element

controlB.description: Control position relative to the parent element

controlA.description: Control position relative to the parent element

beta.description: True if this account has beta privelages

show.description: Show this element for the breakpoint provided

bind.description: Apply properties to this element for a particular breakpoint

hide.description: Hide this element for the breakpoint provided

hoverColour.description: Set the colour of the gui on hover

gridConstraint.description: Quick and dirty way of setting up child elements to follow a simple grid alignment

canvasSize.description: If bigger than 1,0,1,0, scrollvars will be visible

delete.description: Sends a DELETE request. If callback is provided, this function is nonblocking and returns nil. If callback is not provided, this function yields and returns statusCode, body.

put.description: Sends a PUT request. If callback is provided, this function is nonblocking and returns nil. If callback is not provided, this function yields and returns statusCode, body.

post.description: Sends a POST request. If callback is provided, this function is nonblocking and returns nil. If callback is not provided, this function yields and returns statusCode, body.

get.description: Sends a GET request. If callback is provided, this function is nonblocking and returns nil. If callback is not provided, this function yields and returns statusCode, body.

pointA.description: Position of where the line starts relative to the parent element.

lineAlpha.description: An alpha value of 1.0 is completely visible, 0.0 is invisible.

pointB.description: Position of where the line ends relative to the parent element.

position.description: Position relative to the parent element

backgroundAlpha.description: An alpha value of 1.0 is completely visible, 0.0 is invisible.

size.description: Size relative to the parent element

absolutePosition.description: Absolute position in pixels from the top left of the screen

getClient.description: Returns the client for the matching name or id you provide

clients.description: A readonly list of clients, excluding local client when offline

localClient.description: The current local client, nil when unauthenticated

removeColour.description: Removes any set colour at the index provided

setColour.description: Sets the colour of text onwards from the provided index

clearColours.description: Removes any set colours at all indexes

colours.description: Returns a table of {index, colour} (e.g: {{1, colour(1,0,0)}, {3, colour(0,1,0)}})

textShadowColour.description: The text shadow colour, rendered as a blurred backing.

textAlpha.description: 0.0 makes the text fully transparent and invisible.

textMultiline.description: When true, user can input newline characters.

textAlign.description: Determines the rendered text is aligned

textShadowSize.description: When 0, no shadow is rendered. Increasing this value will determine how much the shadow spreads.

textWrap.description: When true, text wraps onto a new line with new line characters.

textDimensions.description: Gets the bounds of the text

textEditable.description: When true, the user can input into this box

setRenderer.description: Sets the renderer used by this client

getRenderers.description: Returns the list of supported renderers on this client

finish.description: Position where the gradient ends, relative to the top left corner of this element.

strokeAlphaB.description: An alpha value of 1.0 is completely visible, 0.0 is invisible.

backgroundAlphaB.description: An alpha value of 1.0 is completely visible, 0.0 is invisible.

start.description: Position where the gradient begins, relative to the top left corner of this element.

traceback.description: Returns a string with a traceback of the stack call.

getOutputHistory.description: Returns a table of dictionaries: {time, message}

changed.description: Fired when a property is changed.

state.description: Mostly for internal use, represents what the user is currently doing.

interface.description: Workshop level interface, renders above the teverse.interfave singleton

localTevGit.description: True if a local tevgit repo is in use

loadDashboard.description: Resets the environment and loads the default Dashboard app

reload.description: Resets the environment and reloads the loaded app

loadString.description: Resets the environment and loads the Lua string provided as an app.

getSource.description: Returns the source code of the loaded app or nil if no app is loaded.

loadScript.description: Resets the environment and loads the Lua file at the provided path as an app.

loadWorkshop.description: Resets the environment and loads the default Workshop app

prompt.description: Prompts the user to select a Lua file, this method then triggers app:loadScript(path)
